[normal]Written evidence submitted by PlaceShapers[bold]1.[bold]              [bold]Background[bold]1.1
[normal]              
[normal]Pla
[normal]ceShapers is a network of over
[normal] 100 community-based housing associations formed in 2008. Between us we own more than 700,000 homes 
[normal]and provide 
[normal]services to more than two million people. These include health services, 
[normal]social care and a range of
[normal] community services. 
[normal]1.2
[normal]              
[normal]Together we complet
[normal]ed over 40,000 new affordable homes between 2008 and 2012 and we collectively plan to invest around £5bn
[normal] to deliver a further 32,000
[normal] homes by 2015. As an alliance, our views therefore represent those responsible for over a quarter of the sector’s housing stock. Details of our members and more about what we do can be found on our website: 
[normal]www.pla
[normal]ceshapers.org
[normal] 
[normal]  
[normal]1.3
[normal]              
[normal]We are pleased to provide this submi
[normal]ssion to assist the
[normal] Committee’s inquiry into the impact of changes in the provision of support to meet housing costs in the reformed welfare system
[normal]. In doing so, we have 
[normal]included evidence
[normal] from our
[normal] members (some of whom may have made their own submissions to the inquiry) 
[normal]on the emerging 
[normal]effects of changes
[normal] implemented
[normal]. We have also drawn on 
[normal]feedback we provided to CLG and DWP staff in January of this year when invited to discuss our concerns about th
[normal]e planned reforms.
